  p One of his friends was raving about Facebook. So he began recording testimonials with teachers and putting them out as Facebook ads:
  video(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/dad1.mp4" class="img__65" playsinline="playsinline" preload="auto" controls="controls")
  p The ads looked solid but the return was poor. I mentioned that he should try out other ad platforms. Instead, he went deeper into Facebook.
  p He watched YouTube videos, signed up for webinars, and even bought an online course. The ROI slowly improved, but it still was far from cost effective. To a worm in horseradish the world is horseradish.
  //- p Dad remained adamant Facebook would come good.
  img(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/dad1b.png" alt="Marketing Examples Product Hunt").img__50
